# Project Architecture

This file describes the target structure of the workspace. It is a reference architecture, not a requirement that every file already exists.

```text
books/
  _template/
    rules/
      project.mdc
      style.mdc

  <project_id>/
    rules/
      project.mdc
      style.mdc

    outline.md
    characters.md
    world-rules.md        # optional
    timeline.md           # optional

    chapters/
      ch01.md

    plans/
      ch01_plan.md

    critique/
      ch01_critique.md

    revisions/
      ch01_revision.md

    memory/
      events.md
      relationships.md
      foreshadowing.md
      mistakes.md

system/
  prompts/
    planner.md
    writer.md
    critic.md
    editor.md
    memory-updater.md
  mistakes/
    planner-mistakes.md
    writer-mistakes.md
    critic-mistakes.md
    editor-mistakes.md
    memory-updater-mistakes.md
```

## Notes

- `books/_template/` is the reusable starter structure for new projects.
- `books/<project_id>/rules/` stores local rules for a specific book or series.
- Local project rules define style and narrative parameters for that project.
- `system/prompts/` stores reusable role prompts for workflow stages.
- `system/mistakes/` stores agent-specific cross-book mistakes, such as `writer-mistakes.md`, which are loaded through the matching prompt.
